headline: AI Tech Lead | M.Sc. in AI & Data
creator: False
bio:
As a visionary Data Scientist and Engineer, I am committed to empowering decision-makers with actionable insights to drive business success. I have proposed, designed, and developed data-driven solutions that have impacted millions of users across various industries, including Telecommunications and Insurance.

With a passion for innovation and a drive to create value, I am devoted to developing cutting-edge technologies that disrupt traditional business models and drive growth. As a tech-savvy enthusiast, I am constantly exploring new ways to harness the power of AI and machine learning to revolutionize industries and improve the lives of people.

Beyond my professional pursuits, I am an entrepreneurship passionate, startup enthusiast, and innovation-seeker, constantly seeking new opportunities to push boundaries and make a positive impact on the world.

ENTJ.

name: Sergei Patrushev
headline: Senior Software Engineer at EPAM Systems with expertise in AWS and Java development.
creator: False
school_2: Tyumen State Oil and Gas University
bio:
As a Senior Software Engineer at EPAM Systems, I work on the server-side development of Java enterprise software solutions for various clients and industries. I am involved in the entire software development lifecycle, from model design and system architecture to product testing and client communication.

With about five years of experience in Java development, I have gained proficiency in Core Java and EE concepts, such as JMS, JPA, ORM, JDBC, and REST API. I have also developed RESTful APIs using Java 8/17 and Spring/Spring Boot frameworks, and worked with relational databases and data modeling (PostgreSQL and Oracle), as well as messaging (RabbitMQ, Kafka).

Additionally, I have acquired multiple certifications in English, AWS, and solutions architecture, demonstrating my commitment to continuous learning and professional development. I have also applied my knowledge and skills to various business applications, such as e-commerce, banking, and finance, delivering high-quality and scalable solutions that meet the clients' needs and expectations.

I am comfortable working in Agile/Kanban environments, collaborating with cross-functional teams.

name: Igor Iurov
headline: Technical Support Team Lead
creator: False
bio:
Hello! 
I inspire people to work together as a team. I have gained the larger part of my experience while working as a project supervisor for Bosch Service Solutions.

It began as our OPM (operations project manager) had left his position so a vacancy was opened. The top managers were looking for a person for this OPM position. There was several candidates for this position, but the project team made their choice: they created a petition to the Top Managers with a requirement to get OPM position for me. There were 47 signatures (of 52 employees in the project at the moment of petition) below this petition. After this petition I got the position.
I'm proud of this situation not because of got the OPM position. I'm proud that my work on supervisor position was so good that people believed in me and wanted to see me on the position of OPM.

name: Valery Borisov
headline: Middle+ C# Developer
creator: False
school_1: Kazan National Research Technical University named after A.N.Tupolev – KAI
bio:
1. JSC "SMP-Neftegaz"
1.1 Simulator for education purposes for Kazanorgsintez PJSC. 
	This is a desktop WPF application which can emulate some emergency situations with chemical facilities and helps to remember all actions to eliminate all consequences according to safety rules. First expirience in corporate developing and code review.

1.2. Powerlifting champinoship
	Another simple WPF application developed as information table for championship (Round result, time and overalltable). Stores every championship as separate entity. Composed of desktop app with SQL Server database (LocalDB). This project was made all by myself.

2. CJSC TaxNet
2.1. Taxnet-Referent
	Is a desktop WPF application intended for sending various electronic documents for different government authorities, such as Tax Authority, Social Insurance Fund and etc. This documents signed by electronic sign. Application use by government organizations or private companies. Developing documents layout using XSLT-transformation. Developing new changes in FLC and big refactoring. FLC (Format Logic Control) - is a huge library designed to checking users' documents according to authority requirements and decoding (parsing). Developing a new document format supporting for Social Insurance Fund. I've developed with my teammates a new lib (called Sedo) for all document processing routines (parsing, cryptography and etc.) in new rails. Almost fully managed this big task as a Feature Lead.

2.2. Declaration.Online
	Is a WEB-browser analogue of Taxnet-Referent. Designed using ASP.NET (backend) + React.js (frontend). In this project I gained a lot of experience with Web development in C# and raised my professional level to middle.

BTW, during all my time in Taxnet I've growed up a several junior developers and I really proud and thankful about their work.

3. SKB Kontur
Kontur.Focus.API
	Kontur.Focus is a WEB-application intended for checking vary companies. It enables users to take an assessment how fair is the organization to partners and government. This awesome service is being developed by a lot of people. Therefore, Focus consist of several different subteams which is disinged diffenrent directions.
	My subproject - API. My tasks here:
	- developing a new API methods for new business pourposes. For instance, a new method that finds an affiliated companies by current company;
	- infrastructure tasks, such as transfer microservice from old hosting platform to a new one;
	- developing high-load data storages which is represented as microservice, but stores data in RAM for fast time of response.

name: Vladimir Ivanyutenko
headline: Robotics Researcher
creator: False
bio:
C++, Git, Java, Python Programming, PostgreSQL , React JS, JS, Css + HTML, Golang.
Developed a solution for capturing a cylindrical object with a manipulator using a cloud of points and assigning a priority to capturing an object using a printed number.
Developed a navigation system for the robot dog unitree A1 based on inertial visual odometry, using only realsense d435i for this.
Used various path planners like DWA,TEB.
Segmented a point cloud in order to find a safe place for a drone to land. A scientific article was written about this https://elibrary.ru/item.asp?id=46309094
Worked with various microcontrollers like rasberry pi and programmed STM32 debug boards in CUBE IDE and Keil. I can read circuit boards, worked in Altium Designer.
Used various CAN,UART,I2C interfaces.
I have experience with databases and various TCP/UDP network protocols.
Worked with Docker, wrote unit and integration tests.
Worked with various data transfer protocols and processing data from sensors. Engaged in the implementation of ROS autoware.
I was engaged in various developments in the field of robotics, worked with various lidars, processed point clouds, prescribed direct and inverse kinematics.
I have experience with linux OS, mainly Ubuntu. Worked with various versions of ROS.
Wrote a driver for an explosion-proof flame detector. The freeRTOS real-time operating system was actively used in this project.
Collaborated with Yuri Panchul, he now uses my work everywhere https://hsto.org/getpro/h
abr/upload_files/e1e/cf0/31c/e1ecf031
ccf787e15c627bddd4999012.png. I programmed FPGA boards, implemented various algorithms for them, read articles and prepared various materials for his "synthesis school".
Participant of the international competition "Eurobot".
Winner of the All-Russian NTI Olympiad in the field of "Intelligent Robotic Systems".
I study in absentia in a distance format

name: Svetlana Kuzmina
headline: Quality Assurance Engineer | Automation & Manual testing | 6+ YoE
creator: True
bio:
I have over 6 years of experience as a Quality Assurance Engineer, working on both websites and mobile apps. My job involves testing these platforms manually and also using automated methods.

I'm skilled in using different tools to ensure everything functions properly. For automating user interfaces, I use Selenium WebDriver, and for automating APIs, I use Rest Assured. When it comes to testing APIs, I'm comfortable with Postman, Charles, and SOAP UI. This means I can thoroughly check that web services and user interfaces are reliable, work well, and perform fast.

My background in manual testing, combined with a smart approach to automation, helps me streamline testing processes. This not only speeds up product releases but also ensures we keep up high quality, even when things are moving quickly.

I like to make the world better through improving the products around us. As a Quality Assurance Engineer I save users from thousands of things that could have gone wrong and spoilt their day. 

Let's connect and share insights on industry trends and create meaningful partnerships.

name: Ilia Sevostianov
headline: Computer Vision Engineer
creator: False
bio:
У меня большой опыт работы программирования на Python и C++, а также глубокое понимание методов и инструментов компьютерного зрения, таких как OpenCV, PyTorch, TensorRT и калибровка датчиков. 

Я хорошо разбираюсь в обучении, настройке и оптимизации нейронных сетей, а также имею опыт квантизации нейронных сетей для повышения производительности. Мой опыт работы в проектах по автономным технологиям, включая разработку автономных систем для грузовиков и водных транспортных средств, систем предупреждения о сходе с полосы движения и точной посадки БПЛА, демонстрирует способность применять мои технические навыки в реальных приложениях. 

Кроме того, я всегда стремлюсь к получению новых знаний и опыта, что делает меня ценным активом для любой команды.

name: Bulat K.
headline: Software Engineer, iOS Developer
creator: False
bio:
I made my first ever iOS app in Objective-C when I was 15, the app now has ~100k MAU (combined iOS and Android audience). Since that time I'm making my way though software engineering field, which I enjoy very much. During last couple of years I've had experiences making my own projects by myself, prototyping and developing apps start-to-end as part of a small team for other people, being a part of a large team of 100+ iOS developers, and managing and mentoring my own team of developers. 

At Alfa-bank I've been able to participate in developing our products in many ways: usual product development (prototype, test, implement, repeat!), updating interview process and conducting tech interviews, onboarding new team members and helping them get up to speed, building a process of cross-project collaboration between developers and designers to build a shared UI library and unify the look and feel of all main projects at Alfa-bank, overseeing the development of different features at Payments department (which are some of the most used features in the app), and so on.

Apart from iOS development, I like exploring other programming languages and their features and have some experience with C++/Objective-C++, Java, Scala, Kotlin and Rust. I'm also interested in ways to implement some parts of the app in a cross-platform reusable way and have experience with using shared Kotlin/Native, J2ObjC and C++ libraries.

At any workplace, the most important thing for me is an active iOS community with people eager to check out new stuff as well as to explore old and existing technologies in their full depth. I hope to find a team where everyone is allowed to contribute their experiences and opinions on any process in order to make everyone's life better.

name: Sergei Goriashin
headline: Java Backend Developer
creator: False
bio:
Java Developer с опытом разработки корпоративных backend-решений для Tier 1 операторов связи.
Переписал ключевые модули десктопного приложения в веб-приложение, что увеличило его масштабируемость и доступность. Выполнил миграцию продукта с Oracle на PostgreSQL, обеспечив совместимость и сократив затраты на лицензии. Разработал десятки RESTful API для расширения функциональности и интеграции с внешними системами. 

Обладаю хорошими навыками командной работы. Был тимлидом в команде эксплуатации, поддерживаю коллег и делюсь опытом. Благодаря опыту в поддержке и тестировании всегда уделяю внимание качеству и надежности продукта.

В своей работе использую следующие технологии: Java 8/11, Spring (Spring Boot, Spring MVC), RESTful APIs, SQL (Oracle, PostgreSQL), JPA/Hibernate, Liquibase, JUnit, Mockito, Jenkins, Grafana, Git

name: Vladislav Lipatov
headline: Front-end enthusiast, musician @ Infomediji
creator: False
bio:
Hi, I'm Vlad - fan of web technologies and good music.

My job is to get things done. How do I achieve that? I communicate, I teach, I code.
I prefer simple solutions, and I find it a challenging and inspiring task: it's always easy to make a system complex, but can you make it simple?
I'm good at making things from scratch, take ownership and responsibility. Of course, I have weaknesses too: I can be not that meticulous about small details, because I like working on big and complex tasks. 
I'm friendly, easy-going, equitable, enthusiastic.

In my spare time I teach my friends front-end development, code some libs for solid-js, torture myself in the gym, play some instruments and make music.

Check out my music:
- https://open.spotify.com/artist/7EE73G7JGyX31LIGSoqq8q
- https://open.spotify.com/artist/2Lv1eDziR9Rca0sxb3uwuk

----------------------------
Favorite tech stack: solid-js for UI, SCSS for styling, bun for server, typescript.

Technologies, tools and libraries I used:

- React, Next, SolidJS, Lit, Svelte, Astro
- SCSS, tailwind, styled-components, emotion
- *-testing-library, jest, vitest, hermione, cypress, playwrite
- Redux, mobx (MST), zustand, effector
- vite, webpack, rollup
- github actions, docker
- Nest.js, node, deno

... and many others unpopular things

school_2: Baltic State Technical University "VOENMEH" named after D.F. Ustinov
bio:
Tech Lead & Backend Golang Engineer

In IT since 2014, I am a Tech Lead & Senior Backend Engineer with 10+ years of experience in software development, specializing in Golang. I develop and maintain backend systems for fintech, gambling, and anti-fraud solutions, focusing on performance and reliability. Besides coding, I enjoy mentoring engineers, conducting technical interviews, and course tutoring.

In recent years, I have led a backend team, contributed to microservices architectures, optimized databases, and performed event-driven systems using Kafka & PostgreSQL. I have experience in both startups and large enterprises, adapting quickly and delivering results in fast-paced environments. Before Golang, I programmed in Java in banking and finance. I also have experience in frontend development with React & Redux, which helps me better understand full-stack architectures.

I have a degree in Computer Science from Baltic State Technical University, where I also participated in competitive programming contests. This experience sharpened my problem-solving skills and ability to write efficient algorithms under time constraints.

Key Achievements:
1. Delivered MVP of an anti-fraud system in 2 months, improving fraud detection efficiency.
2. Fixed 50+ security vulnerabilities using static code analysis (Semgrep).
3. Led a team of engineers, mentoring juniors and conducting 60+ technical interviews. 
4. Tutored IT courses for 50+ students (4 groups), covering algorithms, concurrency, and backend development.
5. Developed a desktop application from scratch, automating manual processes and reducing task time from 7 days to 15 minutes.

Skills:
Backend: Golang, PostgreSQL, Kafka, Redis, gRPC, REST.
DevOps & Cloud: Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD (GitLab), ELK, Prometheus, Grafana.
Other: Code reviews, system design, technical mentoring, IT education.

📩 Let’s connect: rmk140987@gmail.com • https://t.me/rmk1409

bio:
I'm passionate about exploring new technologies and bringing them to life in practical, industry-changing applications. My journey started with a detour from game development into developing mixed reality solutions for construction when VR was still in it's infancy, but ended up as something much bigger than i ever expected. 
What drives me is seeing innovative ideas transform into robust solutions that make a real difference in how people work. I've had the privilege of leading teams that turn cutting-edge concepts into reliable tools used by strategic companies. 
I believe in pushing technological boundaries while staying focused on practical results. Always eager to tackle new challenges and explore emerging technologies that can create meaningful impact in real-world applications.

name: Serge Kazmirchuk
location: St Petersburg, St Petersburg City, Russia
headline: Programmer, Arranger, Sound Designer
creator: False
bio:
2001-2004 studied as a carpenter - cabinetmaker, carpenter - furniture, carpenter - 4th grade machine operator. Graduated with honors.
2004-2006 military service.
Resigned from the army in May 2006. That same summer I entered Gukit to major in feature film director. Got in without any problems. He completed an internship as an assistant director with Ilya Andreevich Khrzhanovsky, in preparation for the filming of the film DAU. After a year and a half, he left the university, due to the futility of the profession, and went to work as a cabinet maker.
Worked in various private carpentry workshops from 2007 to 2011.
The tile laying master who worked at my home offered to join him as a partner. There was no work at that time and I agreed. Together we started renovating apartments, mainly laying tiles. Periodically worked in construction companies. In 2012, I became interested in music and began taking classes at music schools. Helped at the music school with sound equipment and acoustics.
I play guitar, bass guitar, and am interested in creating electronic music and programming it. I communicate with English-speaking musicians via the Internet.
Have some experience working abroad (Poland)
